m\": \"Keleti\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keleti is not only the world's oldest living Olympic champion but also Hungary's greatest Olympic gymnast, with a remarkable total of 10 medals, including five gold.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999989900903171, \"rank\": 5.2375157458712e-07, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Keleti\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's oldest living Olympic champion\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"a remarkable total\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"10 medals\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"five gold\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is a symbol of the Olympian ethic and the idea that sportsmen and women can become models for many people to follow,\\\" says Samu Szemerey, curator of the Olympic Exhibit in Budapest.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 888, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999997352588603, \"rank\": 2.6474040075237463e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/As-Samu\", \"score\": 0.9999999195215455, \"rank\": 8.045972196013805e-08, \"text\": \"Samu\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/As-Samu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/As-Samu\"}, {\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7342896949696872e-13, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"sportsmen\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"models\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"curator\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Exhibit\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being born in 1921 meant Keleti would lose many of her prime years to World War II, but being born Jewish meant the potential for much bigger danger.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Keleti\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"her prime years\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"much bigger danger\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The war forced her into hiding \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 her father and other relatives were killed at Auschwitz.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1283, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auschwitz_concentration_camp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.04523991381581e-14, \"text\": \"Auschwitz\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auschwitz_concentration_camp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auschwitz_concentration_camp\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The war\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"hiding\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"her father\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"other relatives\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the war, Keleti returned to competition, but injury ruled her out of the 1948 Olympics in London.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1391, \"end\": 1397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999977253538, \"rank\": 1.269837923397377e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"Keleti\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1316}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1352}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1948 Olympics\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was at the 1952 Olympics in Helsinki \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 which had been due to host the 1940 Games and was still healing from its own war wounds \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 that she made her mark.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0339150466818914e-11, \"text\": \"Helsinki\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1952 Olympics\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1429}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1940 Games\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1487}, {\"ngram\": \"its own war wounds\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"her mark\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1560}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although already in her thirties, Keleti dazzled the audience in Helsinki and beyond with her performances.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0339150466818914e-11, \"text\": \"Helsinki\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her thirties\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"Keleti\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"the audience\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"her performances\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won gold for floor exercise, silver in the team all-round event, and two bronzes \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 on the uneven bars and in the team portable apparatus event.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"floor exercise\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"all-round event\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"the uneven bars\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"the team portable apparatus event\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three more medals at the 1954 World Championships in Rome set her up for the 1956 Melbourne Olympics, and Keleti seized her chance for greater visibility.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1875, \"end\": 1879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9497330757667818, \"rank\": 0.05273586422612556, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1956_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.190062465795006e-22, \"text\": \"1956 Melbourne Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1956_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1956_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1956_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0